Updates README.md to document Phase 4.5 (PR22-27) alongside the
existing delivery workflow, per the original proposal doc's section 10.

- Intro: added the proposal doc's exact framing paragraph (patient
  check-in via rounding, not just button-press requests; existing
  patient UI kept as a bedside safety display / manual input channel).
- New 'rounding workflow architecture' mermaid diagram, kept separate
  from the existing delivery architecture diagram rather than merged
  into one, mirroring how ROUNDING_ALLOWED_TRANSITIONS is kept as its
  own dict in robot_service.py -- the doc for the two ought to look as
  separate as the code does.
- Feature table: added the 7 rounding-related rows (domain model,
  services, API, simulation script, UI, analytics/Grafana), bumped the
  pytest count from 159 to 249 (actual current collected count).
- Data model: extended the ER diagram with rounding_sessions /
  patient_interactions / nurse_escalations and care_requests' new
  source / rounding_session_id columns; added prose bullets for the
  three new tables.
- Analytics / Grafana sections: added the two new endpoints (with
  example responses) and two new dashboards.
- New 'run_simulated_rounding.py' walkthrough section, same structure
  and same safety-gate framing as the existing run_simulated_delivery.py
  section.
- API endpoint table: added all /rounding/* and /escalations/* routes.
- Roadmap: added a Phase 4.5 row; Current Limitations and the
  未実装 table both got a line noting real speech/person detection
  remains out of scope by design.

No code changes in this PR -- README.md only. Verified: 233 non-pybullet
tests still pass (README isn't parsed by any test); both mermaid blocks
have balanced brackets/parens (the ER diagram's brace 'imbalance' is
expected crow's-foot notation, present in the pre-PR28 diagram too).
